OBITUARY GUESTBOOK DIRECTIONS PRINT PAGE Obituary FRANKLIN ---- Amanda Jean Kelley, 43, of W. Bow Street, passed away at her home on Monday, April 28, 2025. Amanda was born on December 1, 1981, in Keene, the daughter of Randall and Rebekah (Forman) Carpenter. Amanda is survived by the love of her life, Patrick Kelley, son Aiden Kelley, daughter Alexis McCormack, granddaughter Everleigh McCormack, brother Spencer Carpenter, sister Hannah Carpenter, her parents Randall and Rebekah and two nieces. A Celebration of Life will be held at a later date. For those who wish, the family suggests that memorial donations in Amanda’s name be made to the American Pain and Disability Foundation, 1075 Broad Ripple Avenue, Suite 389, Indianapolis, IN 46220 or Monadnock Kitty Rescue & Adoption, 11 Plantation Drive, Jaffrey, NH 03452. Wilkinson-Beane-Simoneau-Paquette Funeral Home & Cremation Services/603Cremations.com, 164 Pleasant St., Laconia, NH, 03246, is assisting the family with arrangements. For more information and to view an online memorial, please visit wilkinsonbeane.com. Directions to Funeral Home 164 Pleasant Street Laconia, NH 03246 603-524-4300
